items.text:
Actors, be honest for a second. 

Have you ever looked at your headshot and thought:

‚ÄúThis doesn‚Äôt feel like me.‚Äù

Not bad.

Not unattractive, perhaps very much attractive but does not feel like YOU.

Just‚Ä¶someone else.

A shinier version.

A more ‚Äúmodel-y‚Äù version.

A version casting will never meet in real life.

And that actually hurts your chances.

Because when your headshot does not look like you, casting feels the disconnect immediately.

They call you in expecting that energy‚Ä¶ and a different one walks through the door. 

The gap breaks trust. 

Most headshot sessions create this problem because there‚Äôs:

No preparation

No real conversation 

No clarity around what you want to convey to casting

Just ‚Äústand there, soft eyes, chin down‚Äù and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!

Sometimes the issue isn‚Äôt the photo, it‚Äôs the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there‚Äôs

X No guesswork

X No over-performing

X No leaving the session hoping there‚Äôs one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs your sign.

Comment or DM me: Let‚Äôs talk headshots and I‚Äôll DM you so we can chat!

Let‚Äôs talk and see if you actually need an update or not.

Actor mark your calendars and improve your craft for February 14th‚Äîa day filled with creativity, collaboration, and cinematic magic! 

Join us for an incredible opportunity to learn, network, and bring your film aspirations to life alongside fellow passionate creatives. 

This free introductory filmmaking workshop in Los Angeles is your chance to connect with filmmakers who are just as excited about storytelling as you are. Dive into the world of filmmaking, where you'll not only share ideas and inspire one another but also roll up your sleeves and create unforgettable movies together. At Empowering Filmmakers, we believe that everyone has a story to tell. We provide everything you need to make your vision a reality‚Äîstate-of-the-art cameras, lighting, props, costumes, and even locations. Stage West Playhouse along with director Mathew Root and assistant director Jacob Mandelin are thrilled to announce auditions for "The Glass Menagerie".

IMPORTANT DATES:
Audition Dates: February 6 at 7 PM and February 8 at 1 PM, at the playhouse
Show Dates: April 24-26

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS:
Auditions will consist of cold readings. Video auditions will be accepted until 1 PM on February 8. Video auditions must include your name, address, phone number and email, as well as if you are auditioning for a specific role. Please include any conflicts you have between audition dates and show dates. Video auditions can be emailed to mattroot1274@gmail.com.

SYNOPSIS:
Tennessee Williams‚Äô The Glass Menagerie is a poignant memory play about family, dreams, and the painful tension between illusion and reality.

Set in a small St. Louis apartment during the 1930s, the story is narrated by Tom Wingfield, who looks back on his youth living with his domineering mother Amanda and his fragile, painfully shy sister Laura. Amanda, abandoned years earlier by her husband, clings to memories of her Southern belle past and is determined to secure a future for Laura, whose physical disability and extreme anxiety keep her isolated from the world.

Amanda pressures Tom, who longs to escape his monotonous warehouse job and pursue a life of adventure and writing, to bring home a ‚Äúgentleman caller‚Äù for Laura. When Tom finally invites his coworker Jim O‚ÄôConnor to dinner, the evening unfolds with hope, awkwardness, and heartbreak‚Äîforcing each character to confront their illusions and the limits of their dreams.

ROLES AVAILABLE:
Tom Wingfield (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
Narrator / Son
A restless young man trapped between responsibility and desire for freedom. Tom works in a warehouse to support his family but dreams of becoming a poet and adventurer. He narrates the story from the future, reflecting on the guilt and longing he still carries after leaving his family behind.

Amanda Wingfield (Female, late 40s‚Äì60s)  Mother
A faded Southern belle clinging desperately to memories of her youth and the illusion of gentility. Amanda is controlling, talkative, and fiercely determined to secure a future for her children, especially Laura. Beneath her humor and bluster lies deep fear of abandonment and poverty.

Laura Wingfield (Female, late teens‚Äì20s)  Daughter
Extremely shy and emotionally fragile, Laura has a slight physical disability and crippling social anxiety. She escapes into her collection of delicate glass animals and old records. Gentle, kind, and painfully self-conscious, she embodies vulnerability and quiet hope.

Jim O‚ÄôConnor (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
The Gentleman Caller
Tom‚Äôs coworker and Amanda‚Äôs long-awaited ‚Äúgentleman caller.‚Äù Once a popular high-school hero, Jim is now an ordinary young man with big dreams and relentless optimism. Kind and well-meaning, though sometimes unaware of the emotional impact he has on others.

Questions? Contact the director at mattroot1274@gmail.com.

topComments.text:
Hey Alaina, as you go about getting some headshots, I'd recommend doing a bit of research into what all is required in an industry standard headshot, just so you can make the most of the session when you get one. I so often see people posting their 'headshots' they have just spent money on and I can often see right away that they don't meet industry standard and they have probably wasted their money as they won't be taken seriously. 

If you know going in what you are needing/hoping to get out of a shoot, it might be a great conversation to have with the photographer and give you both the upper hand on getting some great,  usable and helpful shots. Just a thought I thought might be helpful. All the best! :)

items.text:
Audition with Joy!

NOW ENROLLING 

‚Ä¢ in person | **NYC Weekend February 21 & 22**

‚Ä¢ online | **4-class workshops in March **

**FEARLESS AUDITION TECHNIQUE** is

‚Ä¢ A 10 point system for all kinds of auditions with sides‚Äîfrom self tapes to in person‚Äîthat help you audition with JOY and adventurousness

‚Ä¢ Techniques for handling all of the non-acting moments of an audition with confidence and ease

*and most of all*

‚Ä¢ A positive, adventurous mindset that helps you be an artist in your auditions, beat perfectionism and negative self talk, and audition with actual joy. 

Complete info for both workshops here: https://icont.ac/51dSB

***ÔªøKAREN KOHLHAAS ****is an Atlantic Theater Co. founding member, senior teacher, and Off-Broadway director. She was named**** Best NYC Cold Reading Teacher ****and ****Best NYC Monologue Teacher**** by Backstage readers and is the author of 3 books on monologues and auditioning. She offers private classes in monologues, cold reading, advanced acting, and Tennessee Williams online and sometimes in New York City, and guest teaches around the country. Full bio in the links.*

Taking bookings for our Associates Days! 
Next Associates is on MARCH 8th, 11-4! 
Every second Sunday. 
Now at Mountview in Peckham, join our professional level monthly training. 
Meet casting directors, industry creatives, and work hard alongside like minded performers!
Open to EVERYONE! You do not have to be represented by us, this is completely separate to our agency. However, if you are not represented you are always welcome to apply!
Did you know that boys make up almost 50% of our performers attending all our PTC classes, workshops and also our represented clients! If your boy is tired of being the only one in a class of girls, why not give our Associates a try!
Apply here: https://eu.jotform.com/251303690081045

Landmark gay playwright and author of Bent, Martin Sherman will be joining me on stage at The Two Brewers this Wednesday, as we talk through his extraordinary life and career, and what it‚Äôs meant to tell queer stories across the decades.

Born in Philadelphia and educated at Boston University, Martin now lives in London, and his writing has been produced in more than sixty countries. He is renowned for his Tony-nominated landmark play Bent, which opened at the Royal Court and transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, before going on to Broadway starring Richard Gere. The play was later revived at the National Theatre and adapted for the screen in 1998 starring Clive Owen. Bent went on to win the Dramatists Guild‚Äôs Hull-Warriner Award, and remains one of the most vital pieces of queer theatre ever written.

His theatre work spans decades and includes Rose (National Theatre and Broadway), Gently Down the Stream (Public Theater and Park Theatre), Onassis (Novello Theatre), Some Sunny Day (Hampstead), A Madhouse in Goa (Lyric Hammersmith and Apollo), When She Danced (King‚Äôs Head and Gielgud), Messiah (Hampstead and Aldwych), plus Absolutely! (Perhaps), his acclaimed reworking of Pirandello‚Äôs Right You Are (If You Think So) at Wyndham‚Äôs Theatre. He also wrote the Broadway musical The Boy from Oz and created a major stage adaptation of E. M. Forster‚Äôs A Passage to India (Riverside Theatre and BAM). New work continues, with I‚Äôll Be Seeing You premiering at Pitlochry Festival Theatre in September 2026.

On screen, Martin‚Äôs credits include Mrs Henderson Presents (BAFTA-nominated), The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone, Callas Forever, Alive and Kicking, and The Clothes in the Wardrobe (released in the US as The Summer House). He is currently writing Frank and Percy for the screen, with a major cast including Sir Ian McKellen and Roger Allam.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are strictly limited to 100, with all profits supporting Queer Theatre‚Äôs work nurturing queer talent and telling LGBTQIA+ stories.

Friends!

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly The Colorado Film School) invites actors of all ages to participate in our Spring 2026 Open Auditions!

Our student filmmakers are casting for a wide range of short films, narrative projects, and cinematic productions, and we are seeking performers of all backgrounds, ages, and experience levels to help bring these stories to life on screen.

Whether you are a seasoned professional, a student, or someone who simply loves acting, you are warmly invited to audition and collaborate with the next generation of filmmakers.

üìÖ Audition Dates & Times

Friday, February 6, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 5:00 p.m.

Saturday, February 7, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 4:00 p.m.

 

üìç Location

Lowry Studios ‚Äì Community College of Aurora

9075 E. Lowry Blvd.

Denver, CO 80230

 

üé≠ What to Prepare

Please bring a 2‚Äì3 minute prepared monologue for your primary audition.

In addition to the main audition, we will also host Satellite Auditions for specific student film productions:

‚Ä¢ These will take place in rooms throughout the building

‚Ä¢ Auditions are first-come, first-served

‚Ä¢ Actors can sign up to cold read for individual projects

‚Ä¢ We anticipate up to 10 productions casting during this event

‚Ä¢ A list of roles and productions will be available on the day of the audition

‚Ä¢ Participation in satellite auditions is optional, but highly encouraged

 

üìù How to Sign Up

Actors can sign up using the QR code on the flyer or by visiting:

Accessible Web Link:

https://www.ccaurora.edu/open-auditions

(For visually impaired users or anyone unable to scan the QR code, this link provides full access to the sign-up form.)

If you can't find a reserved space that works for you, come anyway during your preferred time. We will work you into the schedule!

We can't wait to see you this Friday or Saturday!

 

üì© Questions?

Please contact:

galina.boulgakova@ccaurora.edu

 üé• Help our students tell their stories through the magic of cinema.

topComments.text: I‚Äôm sorry but this should be posted a minimum of two weeks in advance so that we can plan and prepare for this. Posting this a day before when most of us have either booked ourselves on other agreements or just unavailable due to some other reason does not help either party involved.
I‚Äôm at 11:30am on Saturday. Highly recommend attending this. I‚Äôve done 5 student films.

Identity first. Results second.

If you don‚Äôt identify as an actor‚Ä¶ you won‚Äôt behave like one.

It‚Äôs not about waiting for permission.
It‚Äôs about deciding who you are ‚Äî now.

When your identity shifts, your standards shift.
Your discipline shifts.
Your career shifts.

This is a mindset game.

items.text:
## **NON-UNION DYSTOPIAN SHORT FILM**

**This is a non-profit, socially responsible project.**
**All positions are volunteer-based. No one will be paid.**

This is an **experimental, post-war dystopian short film** exploring themes of **witnessing, loss, and survival** through visual storytelling and minimal dialogue.
The project is **non-profit and volunteer-based**, created as a **socially responsible artistic collaboration** intended for festival submission.

**CHARACTERS**
* **War Photographer (Male, 40s):** A quiet witness carrying the psychological residue of conflict.
* **Officer:** An anonymous extension of a system, defined by function rather than identity.
* **Woman (40s):** A civilian confronting personal loss within an impersonal process.
* **Elara (Female, around 8):** A war-displaced child who has learned to survive through stillness and awareness.
* **Arion (Male, around 8):** A war-displaced child shaped by escape, movement, and caution.

**You may submit your CV and photos.**
**250shortfilm@gmail.com**

NATIONALLY SYNDICATED COURT SHOW IS LOOKING FOR MARRIED & LONG-TERM COUPLES WHO WANT HELP OR CLOSURE

A nationally syndicated court show is seeking real married couples and long-term partners who are on the verge of breaking up and need answers, resolution, or closure.

We are especially interested in couples with years of history and real-life stakes, including shared children, finances, property, or businesses.

Are you and your spouse facing any of the following?

‚Ä¢ Are you married and ready to call it quits, but need answers first?

‚Ä¢ Do you suspect your spouse or long-term partner is cheating?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse accusing you of cheating and/or denying your child?

‚Ä¢ Have years of marriage led you to a breaking point where you need closure?

‚Ä¢ Do you have evidence your spouse or long-term partner has been unfaithful and want to confront them?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse‚Äôs behavior tearing your family or marriage apart?

‚Ä¢ Are bad habits or addictions damaging your marriage and affecting your children?

‚Ä¢ Have ongoing trust issues made it impossible to move forward in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are in-laws or extended family interfering in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are you in a long-term marriage with unresolved financial betrayal or disputes?

‚Ä¢ Are you married with children and need answers for the sake of your family‚Äôs future?

‚Ä¢ Have you reached the final straw in a long-term marriage and need resolution?

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Married couples

‚Ä¢ Engaged couples

‚Ä¢ Long-term couples (4+ years preferred) with real stakes involved

‚Ä¢ Shared children

‚Ä¢ Shared finances

‚Ä¢ Shared property (home, apartment, vehicles)

‚Ä¢ Shared business or major life commitments

‚Ä¢ LGBTQ+ married and long-term couples

WHAT‚ÄôS INCLUDED:

‚Ä¢ One-day court show appearance

‚Ä¢ Couples counseling / marriage counseling support

‚Ä¢ Lie detector testing (if applicable)

‚Ä¢ DNA testing (if applicable)

üëâ All testing and services are provided and paid for by production.

Click the link below or copy and paste to bowser 

[https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/](https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/)

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?

AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare‚Äôs monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical r√©sum√© to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters‚Äô professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Lear‚Äôs eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Lear‚Äôs middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril‚Äôs partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Lear‚Äôs youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool ‚Äî Lear‚Äôs companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s‚ÄìLate 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear‚Äôs: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear‚Äôs descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Gloucester‚Äôs illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play‚Äôs violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìLate 30s
Gloucester‚Äôs legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as ‚ÄúPoor Tom‚Äù to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Goneril‚Äôs husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Regan‚Äôs spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril‚Äôs primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

NOTE: This show and all other productions by this company are unpaid at this time

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

items.text:
F√ºr unseren Kurzfilm ‚Äû7 Floors to Midnight‚Äú suchen wir einen mutigen Hauptdarsteller.

 Idealerweise bist Du √ºber 40. Herausforderung: Du spielst g√§nzlich unbekleidet. Wichtig w√§re mir, dass Du authentisch spielst. Text ist √ºberschaubar, Emotionen sind wichtig.

Es handelt sich um einen hochwertig produzierten Kurzfilm, der international auf div. Festivals eingereicht wird. Das Ziel ist, min. einen Filmpreis zu schnappen ;-)

Du spielst Claus, den Loser. Insgesamt wirkst Du ziemlich verwahrlost, lebst in einer kleinen, r√§udigen Wohnung und bist mit Deine Leben unzufrieden - bis pl√∂tzlich eine nackte Sch√∂nheit an Deine T√ºr klopft. Mutig weil: Es wird eine (angedeutete) Liebesszene mit Kuss geben.

Es ist lediglich ein kleines, professionelles Team beim Dreh anwesend (Closed Set)

Drehort ist in G√∂ttingen in der Nacht vom 28.2. auf den 1.3.

Hotelkosten, Anfahrt (ICE), ggf. Taxitransfer vom Bahnhof, Catering etc. werden selbstverst√§ndlich √ºbernommen. Zudem zahle ich f√ºr diese nicht ganz allt√§gliche Rolle 300,- Euro an Gage.

Bewerbungen bitte mit Bild, Vita und Telefonnummer an sebastian@fesser.tv (bitte KEINE PNs, die gehen hier immer unter!). Stichwort: Claus

items.text: Hallo liebe Filmfreunde, ich bin Gavin 20 Jahre alt und komme aus Stuttgart. Ich beginne im September meine Ausbildung an der Lazi Akademie in Esslingen. Hat von euch jemand Erfahrung damit gemacht oder kennt jemanden der an dieser Akademie studiert hat? H√§tte ein paar Fragen dazu. Und wenn jemand jetzt √ºber die n√§chste Woche Unterst√ºtzung am einem Set braucht, schreibt mich gerne an. Ich bin flexibel und immer auf der Suche neue motivierte Filmleute kennenzulernen. Eine Frage noch, wer von euch geht diesen September noch auf die Schule, und h√§tte Lust sich dort eine WG zu teilen?

items.text:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don‚Äôt provide proof that they‚Äôve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I‚Äôll get back to you ASAP.

You can view UCCS capstone films from the past few years at this link:
[https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e)

Thank you everyone for supporting our student filmmakers!

TONIGHT at The Two Brewers (Clapham) I‚Äôm beyond proud to welcome Martin Sherman on stage for The Show People Podcast LIVE.

Martin is one of the most important voices in queer theatre. His landmark play BENT opened at the Royal Court, transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, went on to Broadway (Richard Gere), and was later adapted for film. It‚Äôs a piece of writing that helped shape how queer lives are seen on stage.

His work spans decades across theatre and film, including ROSE (National Theatre/Broadway) and the BAFTA-nominated screenplay MRS HENDERSON PRESENTS, plus a body of writing that‚Äôs been produced in more than 60 countries.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are strictly limited to 100
üíõ All profits support Queer Theatre‚Äôs work nurturing LGBTQIA+ talent and telling our stories

items.text:
POSITION: Costume character/ Skin performer

RATE OF PAY: Show day ¬£150, Travel day ¬£50, Subsistence ¬£20

DATES: Rehearsals begin 6th April. First show on 22nd April. Last show on 1st November. 50 Dates throughout the year.

LOCATION: National UK theatre tour

DESCRIPTION: We are looking for a Costume character/ Skin performer for a National children's theatre tour of Fireman Sam Live. Male or female dancers are welcome. Must be between 5‚Äô1‚Äù ‚Äì 5‚Äô8" to fit the costume. Candidates must have costume character performing experience and be comfortable dancing in costume. 

The cast member will be expected to assist with load ins/ outs and drive the touring vehicle with the rest of the company. As a result they will need a clean driving licence and be over the age of 21 for insurance purposes.

If interested send CV's to casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

items.text:
[CASTING CALL]

Hi Everyone! 

We are currently looking for 2 male actors for a fantastic opportunity to work on short film that will be 3 day shoot between the 16th-22nd March, located in Liverpool. 

Daniel 18-25. A young, naive robber that is forced by

circumstances to steal from a corner shop. 

Baz 30-60. A shop keeper who is a people person but has had experience with robbers before.

This will be unpaid work as it is a uni project, but food and travel fees may be compensated. It is also good to note that this short will be entered into film festivals.

If you or anyone you know is interested in these roles or have any information regarding the film shoot, please feel free to reach out to us at stocktakefilm@gmail.com

I‚Äôm in the Burbank area. I‚Äôm looking for some type of job in the film industry that doesn‚Äôt require a film - related college degree. Perhaps reception work at a studio or some type of assistant? Maybe some type of behind the scenes work? Curious about any possibly avenue / opportunity. Any help or advice is greatly appreciated! Thanks! üé¨üòä

topComments.text: Did you check any temp agencies?  I know folks who started with them and ended up working at Disney studios...

Honestly no job in the film industry requires a film degree. It requires a good attitude and work ethic. 
I would look into some pa gigs.
If you're looking for consistency then reach out to rental houses for things like reception or even just cleaning cases.
Knowing what you goals are will 10000% garner better advice for you but without knowing whether you want to be an accountant or a contract agent for for dga or in the greens department it's hard to point you in any direction

items.text:
Hi everyone,

It‚Äôs that time of year again! I‚Äôm reaching out to see who is available to serve as a **Celebrity Escort / Handler** for our **Oscars Week event on March 12** ** in Beverly Hills**.

**Event details:**
* **Date:** March 12
* **Arrival time:** 9:45‚Äì10:00 AM (prompt arrival is required)
* **Wrap time:** No later than 5:00 PM
* **Location:** The Cameo, Beverly Hills

**Role overview:**
You will be assigned **2‚Äì3 celebrities for the day** and will escort them throughout the event, including guiding them to the various gift bag tables and activations.

**Attire:**
* All black
* Comfortable shoes (you will be on your feet)

We have some **new and fun activations this year**, and it‚Äôs shaping up to be a great event.

If you are available and would like to participate, please reply and let me know. If you have any friends who may be interested and would be a good fit, feel free to pass this along.

Once availability is confirmed, I‚Äôll add you to the list for March 12 and share next steps closer to the event.

Just email me at heathermarianna@yahoo.com if you are interested

Thank you as always‚ÄîI truly appreciate your help in making these events run smoothly.

Best,
Heather

items.text:
Hey all! My name is Abigail Rees and I‚Äôm one of the producers for the UNCSA short film *Callbacks*!* ***We are currently looking for extras.**

Our shooting dates are F**ebruary 21st, 22nd, and 23rd **of 2026 in **Winston-Salem, NC**. However you do not need to be available all three days, even one day would be great! Snacks will be provided.

*Callbacks* is about a house filled with actors, dancers, and singers waiting for their callbacks, while Logan, the main character, learns to stand up for himself and get them all to leave.

Please send an email to **[callbacksuncsacasting@gmail.com](mailto:callbacksuncsacasting@gmail.com)**** **if you are interested in being an extra!

It's not necessary to have a special skill, dance, sing or play an instrument, but it would be welcome!

Thank you so much for your time!

items.text:
Hello All, 

Following up on my last post ‚Äî

I‚Äôm taking some time to organize my thinking around independent film distribution and wanted to invite questions while I do.

If you‚Äôre stuck or unclear on any part of the distribution process ‚Äî festivals, sales agents, platforms, deliverables, budgets, or contracts ‚Äî you can share your question here:

**IE3 Media Group - Distribution Questions Intake**

[ https://forms.gle/J3Kg2UyYDk3nCjWC7](https://forms.gle/J3Kg2UyYDk3nCjWC7)

I‚Äôll address a small selection publicly in the group over the course of this week.

Appreciate the thoughtful questions. They tend to reveal the real gaps.

OPEN AUDITION for Julius Caesar by secret actors in secret spaces. Reviewed as 'Shakespeare that is thrillingly new and thrums with raw energy' by British Theatre Guide. The promenade performance puts the audience face to face with the acting as actors in the audience and throughout Reading Abbey Ruins reveal themselves as actors during the show.

WHERE: Rehearsal in central London and Reading. Performance in Reading.
WHEN: Saturday 30th May to Saturday 20th June (rest days on Tuesday 2nd June, 9th June and 16th June). Evening performances in the week. Evening and matinee performances on weekends.
REMUNERATION: ¬£12.71 per hour (National Living Wage) for 100 hours of rehearsal and performance (inclusive of holiday pay).
ELIGIBILITY: Open audition for actors 18 years and older. Please contact us if you need any reasonable adjustments to audition.
AUDITION: Please submit a self tape of a monologue or soliloquy from any of Shakespeare's plays.
DEADLINE: Saturday 28th February at 11:59pm
EMAIL: shakespeareunstaged@gmail.com
CALLBACK: Saturday 28th March in central London

#juliuscaesar #shakespeare #secretshakespeare Secret Shakespeare #auditions #actors #acting #auditioning #readingabbeyruins Reading Abbey Quarter

We‚Äôre looking for a Director & a Creative Lead

for an upcoming hybrid documentary project in Kyrgyzstan.

This is not a classic documentary.

It‚Äôs a cinematic, story driven hybrid between documentary, adventure and travel. Real people, real situations, but with a strong creative vision and narrative arc.

We‚Äôre currently assembling the core creative team and are looking for strong storytellers with a clear visual language and a feel for human stories.

CASTING FOR SHORT FILM - LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES
Casting for ‚ÄòI, Me, Merry‚Äô - a 15 minute short film, Family Drama, final year university student project. 

Shooting in Greater Manchester (specific location tbd), Local and nearby talent are encouraged to apply!

Further details for each role can be found in the individual listings/images below, or on backstage (link at the bottom of this post)

CASTING SUMMARY

LEAD

Audrey - Female, playing age 25-30

SUPPORTING

Linda - Female, playing age 40-60

Phil - Male, playing age 40-60

Isobel - Female, playing age 18

Denise - Female, playing age 60-70

Dennis - Male, playing age 60-70

Uncle Tom - Male, playing age 35-50

EXTRAS

All Genders, playing age 35-55

If interested, please contact r.mazurek@edu.salford.ac.uk stating the role in which you are interested, any prior experience, and a head shot. 

OR

Apply through backstage via the link below:

https://www.backstage.com/casting/i-me-merry-3088446/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=navigator_share_api&utm_campaign=casting_call
